    "This correlation could be explained by results from Section 5, which showed that several of the top-performing models (Claude3-opus, Gemini-1.5-pro) generate the shortest bullet points.",
    "In other words, short bullet points could achieve higher scores not because they are short, but because they were generated by better models.",
    "To remove this confounding variable, we measure whether automatic score ∆ (computed above) correlates with bullet point length.",
    "This analysis, summarized in te Length to Delta Corr.",
    "row of Table 4, indicates a non-existent correlation between bullet-point length, and whether the automatic evaluator was biased in its scoring (-0.081 to 0.02)."
